{"author":{"id":"df79d9acb56ef89cd944cc8548377a5d54d09f0704d032bd86e5f202c0cd02f7"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1516712397,"nonce":"Hodvnc3IwjCAXmi+ctjRhz8lOi8=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM1OTc4MzAwMA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1681#issuecomment-359783000"},"message":"@zfrenchee The nuance is in the now largely obsolete rival encodings used in early Solexa/Illumina FASTQ, nowadays all recent data will be following the original Sanger FASTQ convention - called ``fastqsanger`` in Galaxy. Galaxy uses ``fastq`` as base class covering all the variants, and also defines ``fastqillumina`` etc. If these are mixed up, your downsteam analysis will have very misleading quality scores which can mess up SNP detection etc.\n\nFor more background, see https://doi.org/10.1093%2Fnar%2Fgkp1137\n\n@mvdbeek good to hear Galaxy 17.09 has changed the default importing of FASTQ files, I'd missed that news 👍","files":null}]}